## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="39c1f-248">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica di riconoscimento vocale in grado di riconoscere le due frasi, "sfondo *colore*" e "impostata in background *colore*", dove *colore* viene selezionato da un set di colori.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="39c1f-248">The following example creates a speech recognition grammar that can recognize the two phrases, "Make background *color*" and "Set background to *color*", where *color* is selected from a set of colors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="39c1f-249">Diversi tipi utilizzati per compilare la grammatica finale, ad esempio [stringa](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=159733), <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices>, e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="39c1f-249">Various types are used to build the final grammar, such as [String](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=159733), <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="39c1f-250">Gli operatori di cast espliciti nelle chiamate al <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Add%2A> metodi sono facoltativi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="39c1f-250">The explicit cast operators in the calls to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Add%2A> methods are optional.</span></span>  
  
